        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &quot;Pradhan Mantri Matasya Sampada Yojana: Construction of New Grow out Ponds&quot; by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry &amp; Dairying, Government of India, aims to expand fisheries in various urban and semi-urban areas through the construction of new grow-out ponds. Through this scheme, subsidies are provided for the construction of new grow-out ponds to beneficiaries who are engaged in fisheries.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- The scheme provides financial assistance for the Construction of the New Grow-out Ponds. The project cost is ₹7,00,000/- per Hectare.\n- The subsidy will be limited to 40% of the project cost for beneficiaries falling under the General Category.\n- The subsidy will be limited to 60% of the project cost for beneficiaries who are Scheduled Caste (SC) or Women.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to expand fisheries in various urban and semi-urban areas through the construction of new grow-out ponds. Through this scheme, subsidies are provided for the construction of new grow-out ponds to beneficiaries who are engaged in fisheries.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
